The paper deals with routing algorithms in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of planar triangulations and combinatorial structures suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The focus on routing and communication suggests that it may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of coordinate systems and bits suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
